Circadian variation of calcium conductance
To simulate a circadian rhythm in the maximal conductance of the calcium channel, we assumed a sinusoidal waveform with peak and trough times of ZT 3 and ZT 15, respectively:
gCaLðtÞ ¼ 0:15 þ 0:075ðsinð2pðt þ 3Þ = 24Þ þ 1Þ (8)

Spatial model

In cardiac tissue, neighboring cells are electrically coupled through gap junctions. The spatiotemporal evolution of the cellular membrane potential in a 2-D domain can be described by the following reaction-diffusion partial differential equation (PDE):

vV C vt

¼

