We simulated the ORd model over a grid of PCa and GKR-values (Fig. 10 A), where GKR is the maximal conductance of the rapid delayed rectiﬁer Kþ current.
The model exhibits EADs for a range of high PCa-values, provided that GKR is low enough. For example, with GKR held ﬁxed at 0.01 mS/mF, the model does not exhibit EADs if PCa < 1.5 Â 10À4 cm/s but does exhibit EADs if PCa is above this value (Fig. 10 B). Thus, if there were a circadian rhythm in PCa such that its value traversed this threshold over the course of the day-night cy-
cle, then the ORd model would predict that EADs would
occur at certain times of the day and not others (assuming

